    ProjectManagement

    This program uses two files to track, add, modify and close issues that arise from a software release.

    Author:
    Chad Lister Date: 11/16/2020

      • rebuildFile

        public void rebuildFile(int order,
                        java.lang.String packN,
                        java.lang.String m,
                        java.lang.String a,
                        java.lang.String d,
                        java.lang.String s,
                        int p,
                        java.lang.String c,
                        boolean newFlag,
                        java.lang.String f)
        This method is responsible for rebuilding the Project.dat file. Eliminates stream corruption errors.
        Parameters:
        order - (int: Represents the work order being added, closed, or modified.)
        packN - (String: Represents the package name associated with the work order.)
        m - (String: Represents the module name associated with the work number.)
        a - (String: Represents the team member assigned to the work order.)
        d - (String: Represents the description for the associated work order.)
        s - (String: Represents the status of the associated work order.)
        p - (int: Represents the priority of the associated work order.)
        c - (String: Represents the comments associated with the work order.)
        newFlag - (boolean: Represents or not this is a new record being added.)
        f - (String: Represents any changes to this record.)
